<concept id="concept_FAFDCB5BC3864E738EE94DFD0478CF59" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>About this Manual</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>This manual describes how brokers can support service suppliers in establishing relationships to customers with <ph
                    product="oscm_ce"><ph conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Name"/> (<ph
                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/></ph>) <ph
                    product="oscm_ee">FUJITSU Software Enterprise Service Catalog Manager, hereafter referred to as <ph
                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/></ph>.</p>
            <p>This manual is structured as follows: </p>
            <p>
                <table colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
                    <tgroup cols="2">
                        <colspec colname="col2" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col3" colnum="2" colwidth="1.33*"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2">Chapter</entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Description</entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../../Shared/concepts/c_IntroExtended.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Outlines the role of a broker in <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                    /> and gives an overview of the broker's tasks.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../MarketableServices/c_MSIntro.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                    >Describes the basic concepts of services and explains how to publish services to a marketplace.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../CustomerManagement/c_CMIntro.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                    >Describes the different tasks involved in customer management.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Billing/c_BillIntro.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Describes how <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                    /> supports brokers in calculating and collecting their revenue shares.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Reports/c_Reports.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Describes the reports available for brokers in <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/>. </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Reference/r_MenuOptions.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                    >Gives an overview of the menu options relevant for brokers.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../../Shared/reference/r_LDAP_SettingTypes.xml"
                                    /></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                    >Lists the keys to be defined for enabling access to a customer's LDAP system.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../../DevelopersGuide/Reference/r_BillingData.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                    >Describes the elements of an XML file created by exporting customer billing data.</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
